text: Hector Renato Iturrate Azócar (20 March 1922 - 7 June 2021) was a Chilean cyclist. He competed in the individual and team road race at the 1948 Summer Olympics. Iturrate was married to track athlete Eliana Gaete. He was born in Los Ángeles, Chile. Iturrate died on 7 June 2021 in Santiago de Chile, aged 99.Renato Iturrate ==References== Category:1922 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Chile Category:Cyclists
